title: Winifred Atwell - 2002 - Winifred Atwell's Honky Tonk Piano Part

Winifred Atwell - 2002 - Winifred Atwell's Honky Tonk Piano Party

Una Winifred Atwell (27 February or 27 April 1910 or 1914 Ã¢â‚¬â€œ 28 February 1983) was a Trinidadian pianist who enjoyed great popularity in Britain and Australia from the 1950s with a series of boogie-woogie and ragtime hits, selling over 20 million records. She was the first black person to have a number one hit in the UK Singles Chart and is still the only female instrumentalist to do so. (wikipedia)
